## Examples (Good vs Bad)

### Example: Primary Button

✅ **Good – token‑compliant, tailwind‑driven**

```tsx
<button
  className="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-primary px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white shadow-md hover:bg-primary/90"
>
  Get started
</button>
```

❌ **Bad – hard‑coded values**

```tsx
<button
  className="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-[7px] bg-[#6366f1] px-[15px] py-[9px] text-[15px] font-semibold text-white shadow-[0_4px_6px_rgba(0,0,0,0.1)]"
>
  Get started
</button>
```

### Example: Card

✅ **Good – consistent card pattern**

```tsx
<div className="rounded-lg bg-surface p-6 shadow-sm">
  <h3 className="text-lg font-semibold text-primary">Pro plan</h3>
  <p className="mt-2 text-sm text-neutral">
    Perfect for growing teams that need more control.
  </p>
</div>
```

❌ **Bad – random visual choices**

```tsx
<div className="rounded-[9px] bg-white p-[26px] shadow-[0_10px_15px_rgba(0,0,0,0.1)]">
  <h3 className="text-[18px] font-bold text-[#1f2933]">Pro plan</h3>
  <p className="mt-[9px] text-[13px] text-[#4a5568]">
    Perfect for growing teams that need more control.
  </p>
</div>
```

