## Review Checklist

When changing or creating UI:

- [ ] Are all colors token‑backed (no `bg-[#hex]`, `bg-blue-500`, etc.)?
- [ ] Are fonts referenced only via project classes (`font-*`, `text-*`) rather than raw font stacks?
- [ ] Are radii and shadows using standard utilities (`rounded-lg`, `shadow-md`) instead of arbitrary values?
- [ ] Is spacing chosen from the existing scale (or documented utilities) rather than weird one‑off pixel values?
- [ ] If a new pattern was needed, was it added to `design-tokens.ts` and wired through Tailwind?

If all answers are “yes”, the styling is consistent with the design system and safe for future token changes.